15. Glossary Development - Create project glossary
Term	Description
Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System	A centralized digital platform used to report, track, and manage cybersecurity incidents within an organization.
Cybersecurity Incident	Any event that compromises or threatens the confidentiality, integrity, or availability of information systems.
Incident Report	A formal record submitted by a user describing a suspected or confirmed security incident.
Severity Level	Classification of an incident based on its impact and urgency (Low, Medium, High, Critical).
Incident Lifecycle	The complete process of handling an incident from detection to closure.
SOC (Security Operations Center)	A team responsible for monitoring, analyzing, and responding to cybersecurity threats.
SOC Analyst	A security professional who investigates and responds to reported incidents.
Admin (System Administrator)	Authorized personnel responsible for managing users, configurations, and compliance records.
Response Workflow	A structured set of steps followed to mitigate and resolve a cybersecurity incident.
Alert / Notification	A system-generated message informing users or SOC teams about incident updates or critical events.
Audit Trail	A chronological record of all actions performed during an incident for accountability and compliance.
Compliance Documentation	Records maintained to meet regulatory and organizational security requirements.
Risk Analysis	The process of evaluating the potential impact and likelihood of a security incident.
Dashboard	A real-time visual interface displaying incident statistics, severity distribution, and system status.
Authentication	The process of verifying a userâ€™s identity before granting system access.
Authorization	The process of granting permissions to users based on their assigned roles.
SRS (Software Requirements Specification)	A document that defines the functional and non-functional requirements of the system.
UI (User Interface)	The visual elements through which users interact with the system.
Incident ID	A unique identifier assigned to each reported incident.
Status Update	A change in the state of an incident (e.g., New, In Progress, Resolved, Closed).
